        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer355328687" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6512385230938718647">This book kept me riveted! It is told through the eyes of both Tony Hooper and MItchell Norton. It starts in 1995 as Mitchell is being released from prison and goes back and forth from that time frame to 1978, when all the tragedy occurs. <br/><br/><br/>I loved the way that the author draws you in to the story right away, and then slowly dishes you out the details. You know the outcome, because Mitchell was in prison for 17 years - but you don&apos;t know everything that happens in 1978 and those are the details th</span>
  <span id="freeText6512385230938718647" style="display:none">This book kept me riveted! It is told through the eyes of both Tony Hooper and MItchell Norton. It starts in 1995 as Mitchell is being released from prison and goes back and forth from that time frame to 1978, when all the tragedy occurs. <br /><br /><br />I loved the way that the author draws you in to the story right away, and then slowly dishes you out the details. You know the outcome, because Mitchell was in prison for 17 years - but you don't know everything that happens in 1978 and those are the details that you are spoon-fed through out the rest of the book. <br /><br /><br />At the same time you struggle along with Tony as he wades through his memories as well as what he has become because of Mitchell. Along with Linda, the FBI agent who cut her teeth on the Norton case, and has crossed paths with Tony over the years, you hope that he is able to overcome the wall he has put up to keep people from getting too close. <br /><br /><br />I thought this was a great thriller and am looking forward to reading more by this author. <br /><br /><br />Read more: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://booksandneedlepoint.blogspot.com/#ixzz215bBiopf">http://booksandneedlepoint.blogspot.c...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="6512385230938718647" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
